OL,3,CPoliticians 'tone-deaf' as taxpayers'
OL,4,C#35,000 spent on foreign trips
OL,6,FThis involved a visit to a
OL,7,Fconstituency office in London, a
OL,8,Fsession led by the Deputy Speaker of
OL,9,Fthe House of Commons, a chance to meet
OL,10,Fthe General Secretary of the CPA and
OL,11,Fto attend Prime Minister's Questions.
OL,13,FSome feel the travel is hypocritical
OL,14,Fgiven the Government's push for
OL,15,Fislanders to reduce their carbon
OL,16,Ffootprints.
OL,18,FClimate campaigner Nigel Jones said:
OL,19,F"It seems crass and tone-deaf of the
OL,20,Fpeople in high office to be wasting
OL,21,Femissions like that."
